  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You are given an array AAA, consisting of NNN **distinct** integers.\n\nCalculate number of pairs (i,j)(i,j)(i,j) (1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N)(1 \\le i &lt; j \\le N)(1\u2264i&lt;j\u2264N), such that 2\u22c5(Ai\u2295Aj)=Ai+Aj2 \\cdot (A_i \\oplus A_j) = A_i + A_j2\u22c5(Ai\u200b\u2295Aj\u200b)=Ai\u200b+Aj\u200b, where \u2295\\oplus\u2295 denotes bitwise XOR.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line contains two integers NNN \u2212-\u2212 the size of the array.\nThe second line contains NNN space-separated integers A1,\u2026,ANA_1, \\ldots, A_NA1\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b \u2212-\u2212 the elements of the array AAA.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output the number of pairs satisfying constraints.",
    "constraints": [
      "2\u2264N\u22641062 \\leq N \\leq 10^62\u2264N\u2264106",
      "1\u2264Ai\u2264260\u221211 \\leq A_i \\leq 2^{60}-11\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264260\u22121",
      "Subtasks",
      "**Subtask 111 (20 points):** 2\u2264N\u226420002 \\leq N \\leq 20002\u2264N\u22642000",
      "**Subtask 222 (40 points):** 1\u2264Ai\u2264220\u221211 \\leq A_i \\leq 2^{20}-11\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264220\u22121",
      "**Subtask 333 (40 points):** Original constraints."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "4\n1 2 3 6",
        "output": "2",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nThere are 222 pairs (i,j)(i,j)(i,j) satisfying all the conditions.\n\n(i,j)=(1,3)(i,j)= (1, 3)(i,j)=(1,3). Thus, 2\u22c5(A1\u2295A3)=2\u22c5(1\u22953)=2\u22c52=42\\cdot (A_1\\oplus A_3) = 2\\cdot (1\\oplus 3) = 2\\cdot 2 = 42\u22c5(A1\u200b\u2295A3\u200b)=2\u22c5(1\u22953)=2\u22c52=4. Also, A1+A3=1+3=4A_1+A_3 = 1+3 = 4A1\u200b+A3\u200b=1+3=4.\n(i,j)=(2,4)(i,j)= (2, 4)(i,j)=(2,4). Thus, 2\u22c5(A2\u2295A4)=2\u22c5(2\u22956)=2\u22c54=82\\cdot (A_2\\oplus A_4) = 2\\cdot (2\\oplus 6) = 2\\cdot 4 = 82\u22c5(A2\u200b\u2295A4\u200b)=2\u22c5(2\u22956)=2\u22c54=8. Also, A2+A4=2+6=8A_2+A_4 = 2+6 = 8A2\u200b+A4\u200b=2+6=8."
      },
      {
        "id": "sample_2",
        "input": "5\n4 3 9 7 1",
        "output": "1",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nThere is only one pair (i,j)(i,j)(i,j) satisfying all the conditions:\n\n(i,j)=(2,5)(i,j) = (2, 5)(i,j)=(2,5). Thus, 2\u22c5(A2\u2295A5)=2\u22c5(3\u22951)=2\u22c52=42\\cdot (A_2\\oplus A_5) = 2\\cdot (3\\oplus 1) = 2\\cdot 2 = 42\u22c5(A2\u200b\u2295A5\u200b)=2\u22c5(3\u22951)=2\u22c52=4. Also, A2+A5=3+1=4A_2+A_5 = 3+1 = 4A2\u200b+A5\u200b=3+1=4."
      }
    ]
